-- Heidelberger Druck, Infineon, Linde, ThyssenKrupp: German Equity Preview
-- Julie Cruz
-- 2010-06-15T06:21:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/heidelberger-druck-infineon-linde-thyssenkrupp-german-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Germany. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the last close.  
 DAX Index  futures expiring in June lost 0.5 percent to
6,090.5 as of 8:19 a.m. in Frankfurt. The benchmark DAX gained
1.3 percent to 6,125 yesterday.  
 Continental AG  (CON GY): The auto-parts maker wants to sell
more bonds than planned to help repay debt, Handelsblatt said,
citing Chief Financial Officer  Wolfgang Schaefer .  
 Continental plans to sell as much as 4 billion euros ($4.9
billion) of bonds, including a planned sale of between 1.5
billion and 2 billion euros in high-yield notes, the newspaper
said, citing the CFO. The shares gained 1.4 percent to 43 euros.  
      Heidelberger Druckmaschinen AG  (HDD GY): The printing-press
maker said its full-year loss narrowed to 229 million euros from
249 million euros. The shares surged 4.9 percent to 8.71 euros.  
 Infineon Technologies AG  (IFX GY): Europe’s second-largest
chipmaker hired JPMorgan Chase & Co. as adviser on a possible
sale of its mobile-chip unit, Financial Times Deutschland
reported, without saying where it got the information. The
shares rose 2.6 percent to 4.94 euros.  
 Lanxess AG  (LXS GY): Nomura Holdings Inc. lifted its
recommendation on Germany’s largest publicly-traded specialty
chemicals maker to “neutral” from “reduce.” The shares
rallied 3.7 percent to 37.06 euros.  
 Linde AG  (LIN GY): The world’s second-biggest maker of
industrial gases was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at Nomura.
The shares added 0.5 percent to 87.67 euros.  
 ThyssenKrupp AG  (TKA GY): Germany’s largest steelmaker was
raised to “buy” from “hold” at Citigroup Inc. The shares
gained 2.4 percent to 21.56 euros.  
